Package model.Query

Class BaseQuery<R extends IBaseRow<?>>

java.lang.Object
model.Query.SConnection
model.Query.BaseQuery<R>
Type Parameters:
R - The type of Row which a subclass of BaseQuery will produce.
All Implemented Interfaces:
IBaseQuery<R>
Direct Known Subclasses:
TableQuery
public abstract class BaseQuery<R extends IBaseRow<?>> extends SConnection implements IBaseQuery<R>
This abstract class creates an ObservableList (accessible via getRows()) containing type R which depends on an SQL query defined by subclassing constructDsqlQuery().

  • Field Details

    • updateChannels

      private static final Map<String,Set<javafx.beans.InvalidationListener>> updateChannels

    • statement

      protected final Dependable<Statement> statement
      `statement` wraps a Statement which depends on the shared JDBC Connection, and which is dedicated to serving this particular Query. Dedicating a Statement to each Query means that each Query's resultSet can operate without interference from other requests to the JDBC.
      See Also:
      • constructDStatement()

    • sqlQuery

      protected final Dependable<String> sqlQuery
      'sqlQuery' wraps a String to be used as an SQL Query executed in resultSet. This wrapper is constructed as the result of calling constructDsqlQuery() once during BaseQuery's initialization.
      See Also:
      • constructDsqlQuery()

    • resultSet

      protected final Dependable<ResultSet> resultSet
      'resultSet' wraps a ResultSet which by default depends on this BaseQuery's statement and sqlQuery. The wrapped ResultSet will execute sqlQuery. This wrapper is constructed as the result of calling constructDResultSet() once during BaseQuery's initialization.
      See Also:
      • constructDResultSet()

    • resultSetMetaData

      protected final Dependable<ResultSetMetaData> resultSetMetaData
      'resultSetMetaData' wraps a ResultSetMetaData which by default depends on this BaseQuery's resultSet. The wrapped ResultSetMetaData will be extracted from resultSet. This wrapper is constructed as the result of calling constructDResultSetMetaData() once during BaseQuery's initialization.
      See Also:
      • constructDResultSetMetaData()

    • rowsList

      protected final Dependable<javafx.collections.ObservableList<R extends IBaseRow<?>>> rowsList
      rowsList is a wrapper around an ObservableList which holds all the objects generated by resultSet. rowsList depends on resultSet, meaning that whenever resultSet is invalidated, the results of rebuilding resultSet will be used to rebuild rowsList. rowsList is constructed with the result of calling constructDRowsList() once during the initialization of a BaseQuery.

    • invisibleColumns

      public static final Set<String> invisibleColumns
      By default, some columns which are common in the database should not be shown to the user. Those columns are listed here.

    • requestedColumns

      private final javafx.beans.property.ReadOnlyMapWrapper<String,Boolean> requestedColumns
      BaseQuery can store information about what columns its users have requested be shown. However, this information is not acted upon by BaseQuery. This information is stored as String-Boolean entries, mapping whether the requested Column should (true) or should not (false) be displayed.
      It's perfectly reasonable that a version of BaseQuery could be re-negotiated to only expose requested columns. As an example, QueryTableView has private methods which would need changed.

  • Constructor Details

    • BaseQuery

      public BaseQuery(String... channelsToSubscribe)
      BaseQuery can be instantiated with names of channels to subscribe to. When a channel publishes, all BaseQuery's which subscribed to that channel are instructed to re-execute to stay in sync with the Database.
      Generally (see BaseQuery.BQResultSet.invalidated() and WritableTableQuery.WritableTableQueryRow.refresh()), a channel will publish when one of the BaseQuery's subscribed to it pushes an update to the Database.
      This constructor uses a Lambda to express the InvalidationListener which updates the expected columns, whenever the ResultSetMetaData is recalculated.
      Parameters:
      channelsToSubscribe - The String keys to all the channels which this BaseQuery should subscribe and publish to.

  • Method Details

    • constructDStatement

      protected Dependable<Statement> constructDStatement()
      constructDStatement is called once during the initialization of a BaseQuery, to construct a Dependable-Statement which serves the needs of the subclasses of BaseQuery and depends on the shared SConnection JDBC Connection.
      A basic implementation of constructDStatement is provided in BaseQuery which ties into the BaseQuery infrastructure. Overriding this method and subclassing BaseQuery.BQStatement may be an integral part of configuring the Statement you want to use in a subclass of BaseQuery.
      Returns:
      A Dependable Statement configured for use in a BaseQuery.
      See Also:
      • statement
      • BaseQuery<R extends IBaseRow<?>>.BQStatement

    • constructDsqlQuery

      protected abstract Dependable<String> constructDsqlQuery()
      constructDsqlQuery is called once during the initialization of a BaseQuery, to construct sqlQuery.
      This method, and therefore the configuration of sqlQuery, is left up to subclasses of BaseQuery. This allows subclasses of BaseQuery to define Observables which sqlQuery depends on.
      Returns:
      A Dependable-String which will be executed by resultSet.

    • constructDResultSet

      protected Dependable<ResultSet> constructDResultSet()
      constructDResultSet is called once during the initialization of a BaseQuery, to construct a Dependable-ResultSet which serves the needs of the subclasses of BaseQuery.
      A basic implementation of constructDResultSet is provided in BaseQuery which ties into the BaseQuery infrastructure. Overriding this method and subclassing BaseQuery.BQResultSet may be an integral part of configuring the ResultSet you want to use in a subclass of BaseQuery.
      Returns:
      A Dependable wrapping a ResultSet configured for use in a BaseQuery.

    • constructDRowsList

      protected Dependable<javafx.collections.ObservableList<R>> constructDRowsList()
      constructDRowsList is called once during the initialization of a BaseQuery to provide the value of rowsList. constructDRowsList uses BaseQuery<R extends IBaseRow<?>>.BQRowsList as a default implementation in BaseQuery.
      Overriding this method and subclassing BaseQuery.BQRowsList may be an integral part of configuring the rowsList you want to use in a subclass of BaseQuery.
      Returns:
      A Dependable which is stored in rowsList
